                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ravvenn pretty much covered all the great stuff, so I thought I would add a few things I wasn't too hot on.
<br />
Level limit was 30, still is now in beta. Bummer on that, I wanted to progress further since there are only so many times I want to do the newbie quests over again. Hopefully as beta progresses they will raise the cap a bit.
<br />
The Aliance and The Horde are different factions, meaning they dont get to interact. Sucky IMOH, but then I play EQ and not DAoC.
<br />
Getting to other towns to play with your newbie friends is tough tough tough. BUT, they have a pretty great map system that helps you navigate.
<br />
The mini map was broken but they claim it will be fixed and usable soon. (still broken in beta)
<br />
May of the newbie quests are collect these # of items and return them. You dont really get into fun quests untill later. Still there are some really cute quest interactions. Look for NPC comments, got a few laughs out of those. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />
Where is my horse???  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_boohoo.gif" alt="eusa_boohoo.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />
Towns are huge. I can't count how many times I got lost. (mini map will hopefully make it easier) But they are great to look at, so at least you will have a good time looking arround while your lost. Hehe.
<br />

<br />
Food for thought...constructive critisism please.
<br />

<br />
Its really pretty!!  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_dance.gif" alt="eusa_dance.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
