                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't think travel time is that bad, usually there's a small town not very far from where you're fighting if you need but since you can't find banks everywhere you just get used to carrying what you need with you and ignore junk loot (well, at least I never cared about looting stuff since I was expecting them to wipe my characters from Alpha). Griffon rides help if you're going somewhere far and are cool and stuff but after a while you just want to skip them <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />.
<br />

<br />
The only thing that I miss from EQ is the name filter, I'm not much into roleplaying but looking at the names some people choose makes me want to cry <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />. Some people come up with the most stupid names and since you can also play around with caps you see people called iNukeStuff or GnOmEmAgE.
<br />

<br />
The tradeskill system is awesome, if you try a recipe that is way above your skill level you get a guaranteed skill up, no more collecting enough for 100 combines and praying the RNG is on your side. But the hardcore tradeskill junkies won't like it much since you can't master all skills and you need to level to gather components for the higher level stuff.
<br />

<br />
The quest log window is pretty cool too, makes it easy to keep track of all active quests you have, and you'll have lots since their quests actually give decent experience.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Hunter Keawen / Master Kedawen
<br />
&lt;Vis Maior&gt; - Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
